news.title: Windsor Realty acquires four office units in Mumbai’s Santacruz tower for ₹283 crore
news.para: The acquisition involved the purchase of two commercial units from corporate entities including Prism Johnson Ltd and two from the developer's partner. The transactions effectively bring the entire asset under a single ownership, streamlining control and management of the property.

news.title: Gurugram: ED chargesheets Ocean Seven Buildtech's promoter in PMAY housing 'fraud' case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has launched a formal chargesheet against Swaraj Singh Yadav, the mastermind behind Ocean Seven Buildtech Pvt Ltd. This legal move is tied to an extensive money laundering investigation involving alleged financial deceit against homebuyers enrolled in the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana.

news.title: Gurugram civic body's year-end property tax drive nets ₹30 crore in 45 days
news.para: Gurugram's Municipal Corporation has intensified its property tax recovery, collecting Rs 30 crore in the last 1.5 months and exceeding its annual target. The civic body sealed 55 properties and issued 410 notices to defaulters. Efforts are now focused on identifying commercial activities in residential areas to boost revenue.

news.title: MPCB shuts 10 ready-mix concrete plants across Mumbai region
news.para: Authorities have cracked down on air pollution in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region, shutting down 10 ready-mix concrete plants and collecting Rs 84 lakh in fines over two days. Inspections revealed numerous violations of environmental and dust-control norms. Seventeen plants received show-cause notices, and five construction sites faced proposed directions for non-compliance, highlighting ongoing efforts to improve air quality.

news.title: CapitaLand sells Gurugram office asset to EAAA Alternatives for ₹2,050 crore
news.para: CapitaLand has sold a major Gurugram commercial property for ₹2,050 crore. This move is part of its strategy to free up capital and invest in new areas. The company previously sold other IT park assets. EAAA Alternatives, part of Edelweiss Group, made the acquisition. This deal highlights ongoing activity in India's real estate market.

news.title: Chandigarh administration is set to overhaul building bylaws to boost industrial growth
news.para: Chandigarh is set to overhaul its building bylaws to boost industrial growth, with a key reform increasing the permissible floor area ratio (FAR) for industrial plots. Architectural controls will be replaced by zoning parameters for smaller plots, aiming to reduce land loss and enhance competitiveness. The administration is also finalizing plans for the undeveloped Industrial Area Phase III.

news.title: Sumadhura Group invests ₹1,000 crore to develop six residential projects in Bengaluru
news.para: Sumadhura Group is investing ₹1,000 crore in six new residential projects across East and North Bengaluru. These developments are planned for completion by FY26. The projects will offer over 4,000 residential units and more than 400 plots.

news.title: Bengaluru development body razes ‘illegal’ houses in Saraipalya
news.para: Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) demolished approximately 22 'illegal' properties, including godowns and residential sheds, on two acres of notified BDA land in Saraipalya, Thanisandra. Residents, however, claim over 60 structures were torn down, with some presenting property documents and questioning the sudden action.

news.title: Keystone Realtors'  sales bookings down 3% to ₹837 crore in Q3 FY26
news.para: Keystone Realtors has reported a slight dip in sales bookings for the third quarter. However, the company has achieved growth over the first nine months of the financial year. The company launched one project in the quarter and five projects in the nine-month period.

news.title: Show-cause notices issued to 90 illegal ready-mix concrete plants in Gurugram
news.para: Gurugram authorities have taken a strong stand against 90 illegal ready-mix concrete plants, issuing show-cause notices. These steps are part of a broader strategy to combat roadside dust and ensure cleaner air for residents. Meanwhile, the city is actively addressing road repair complaints while also initiating tenders for innovative rainwater harvesting systems.

news.title: What LDA & LMC propose to do with Sahara land, asks Allahabad HC
news.para: The Allahabad High Court has sought details from the Lucknow Development Authority and municipal corporation. The court wants to know their plans for land reclaimed from Sahara India Commercial Corporation Limited in Gomtinagar. This information is being sought without prejudice to Sahara's ongoing petition. The court has fixed the next hearing for January 19.

news.title: Nashik to get incentive FSI for redevelopment: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: Nashik city will soon get enhanced Floor Space Index benefits for redeveloping old buildings. Deputy Chief Minister Eknath Shinde assured this to trade and industry associations. This move aims to speed up urban renewal and upgrade aging infrastructure. Developers had highlighted financial unviability due to lower FSI compared to Thane and Pune.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body to issue notices to 40,000 house tax defaulters
news.para: Prayagraj Municipal Corporation will soon issue notices to 40,000 property owners who have not paid taxes for three years. Those failing to clear dues within 15 days will face property attachment and water supply disconnection. This move aims to boost tax recovery. Buildings will be reopened only after full payment. Breaking seals will lead to legal action.

news.title: Lucknow development body conducts lottery for 1,665 1BHK flats under Atalnagar Yojana
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority held a lottery for 1BHK flats in Atalnagar Yojana.  1,665 flats were allotted through a transparent, live-streamed process.  Applicants expressed relief and joy at securing a permanent home.  The draw for 2BHK flats is scheduled for Friday.  The scheme received over 5,700 applications for the 2,496 flats.

news.title: NGT gives Greater Noida authority one month to file report on illegal constructions
news.para: The Greater Noida Development Authority has failed to submit a report on illegal constructions to the National Green Tribunal. The tribunal has now given the Authority one month to file an affidavit. A former corporator had filed a petition highlighting illegal constructions and groundwater extraction.

news.title: Oberoi Realty, Shree Naman in race for Railway’s 11-acre land in Mumbai's Bandra
news.para: Oberoi Realty and Shree Naman Developers are eligible bidders for a prime 11.21-acre railway land parcel in Mumbai's Bandra. The Railway Land Development Authority set a reserve price of Rs 5,365 crore for the land. This is the third land parcel monetised by RLDA in Mumbai recently.

news.title: SWAMIH Fund helps complete 61,000 homes in stalled projects till December 15
news.para: The SWAMIH fund has  facilitated over 61,000 homes in previously stalled projects. This government-backed initiative is poised to close the gap on more than one lakh homes, thereby benefiting upwards of four lakh people.

news.title: DRA Homes partners with Yubi to establish ₹250 crore secured debt platform
news.para: DRA Homes has joined forces with Yubi Group to establish a ₹250 crore secured debt initiative. This funding is earmarked solely for land acquisition, a strategic move underscored by Ranjeeth Rathod, managing director, who emphasized the importance of institutionalizing land sourcing through secure, non-dilutive capital.

news.title: Patna civic body imposes strict measures to curb construction dust pollution
news.para: In response to alarming air quality levels, Patna’s authorities have introduced stringent guidelines for managing construction debris. The Municipal Corporation is enforcing the use of designated disposal areas and green mesh at all construction sites, aiming to tackle the escalating dust pollution.

news.title: Shree KB Realty buys three-acre land in Greater Noida via auction for ₹122 crore
news.para: Shree KB Realty has secured a prime 3-acre site in Greater Noida for a remarkable Rs 122 crore. This strategic acquisition, completed through an auction conducted by the Greater Noida Authority, is set to pave the way for a  commercial development.
